Paper: hep-th/9401159

Date: 1994-01-31

Title: Remarks on geometric entropy

Authors: J.S.Dowker

Comments: 7p.,uses jyTeX,MUTP/94/2

Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 11 (1994) L55-L60

The recently discussed notion of geometric entropy is shown to be related toearlier calculations of thermal effects in Rindler space. The evaluation isextended to de Sitter space and to a two-dimensional black hole.